MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 364c2b772391e46dba637935c558b9b2, type: 3}
  m_Name: Eagle
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::MythSO
  pageNumber: 119
  mythName: Eagle
  omens:
  - '1. A great shadow sweeps the landscape,

    blotting the sun for a moment.'
  - '2. A flame above, shrieking until it plunges

    to the ground, sending roaring
    fire in

    every direction (d8 blast) and setting the

    area alight. The
    Eagle, Aflame, surveys

    the destruction then makes flight for the

    nearest
    large body of water.'
  - '3. The Eagle, Smouldering, bathing to

    extinguish its feathers. It cannot
    fly for

    another Phase, but can hobble about. A

    crowd, driven from their
    burning homes,

    watch, and protect the Eagle from harm.'
  - '4. The Eagle, Rising, stretches its wings,

    preparing to fly. As it ascends
    it sends a

    gust of wind through the Hex, felling

    wooden structures
    and flattening trees.'
  - '5. The sun seems to swell, then a piercing

    cry. The shape of the Eagle,
    Aflame,

    appears in the sky, just circling for now.'
  - '6. The Eagle, Aflame, dives on the Seat of

    Power, aiming to snatch the
    ruler and

    carry them up into the sun as an offering.

    If this fails
    the next harvest is dire.'
  verse: 'A bird o''flame to claim sun'' s toll

    Crown for crown, gold for gold'
  castEntries:
  - name: The Eagle, Aflame
    statBlock: 'VIG 15, CLA 15, SPI 15, 8 GD

      A2 (huge body), talons (2d8)
      and beak (d12)'
    notes: Wants lots of fire to fuel the sun.
  - name: The Eagle, Smouldering
    statBlock: 'VIG 13, CLA 12, SPI 10, 6 GD

      A2 (huge body), clumsy thrashing
      (d8 blast)'
    notes: Wants to extinguish its burning wings.
  - name: The Eagle, Rising
    statBlock: 'VIG 15, CLA 18, SPI 18, 12 GD

      A2 (huge body), gusts of wind
      (d10 blast)'
    notes: Must dry wings on the wind before flying.
  - name: Protective Victims of the Eagle
    statBlock: 'VIG 10, CLA 10, SPI 7, 2 GD

      See below. They say the Eagle
      means well.'
    notes: 
  flavorTable:
    title: SALVAGED BELONGINGS
    columns:
    - header: In their hands
      values:
      - Broken crutch
      - Crying infant
      - Live chicken
      - Flimsy hoe
      - Rope tied to a goat
      - Lucky beads
    - header: In their backpack
      values:
      - Sack of grain
      - Patchwork quilt
      - Dried fish
      - Bladder of wine
      - Metal pots
      - Herb bundles
  visibleByDefault: 0
  visibleMarkerPrefab: {fileID: 0}
